  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Surgical resection in patients with multiple hepatocellular carcinomas (HCC) remains
      controversial. The aim of this study was to investigate the outcome of a consecutive cohort
      of patients resected for multiple HCC, without macrovascular invasion, in order to identify
      clinically reliable parameters to select patients for surgery.
    </textblock>
